The consistent factor I see in all of these misses, is that BlueSky doesn't talk to or listen to Black users or Black experts in the field of moderation and online communities, about their concerns or recommendations.

This is before we even get to "Do they follow any of those recommendations?"

Black users know this. A lot of non-Black users that have read these same things, and know this too.

I'm not saying that this is BlueSky's strategy! But it's... super weird the way that BlueSky seems to avoid talking to Black folk, or letting Black folk talk about this.

Like I wanna be clear - this is the least real *big* chance for BIPOC, LGBTQIA+, Disabled folks, poor folks, and sex workers to have a community we all exist in semi-harmony together. If Bluesky fails, it WILL schism because every other platform is hostile to 2+ of those groups. 

We gotta make it.

Hate speech cannot be tolerated on this network. Racism should not have any space on this network, whether in posts, usernames, or handles. We demand that content moderation be quick and effective. We will not tolerate racism!

The gay agenda for today: 

✅ Follow the Blacksky feed
✅ Boost Black voices instead of talking over them or for them
✅ Pay the Black users who have been doing so much unpaid work to call out these issues
✅ Don't stop until Bluesky issues a real apology and takes actual steps towards addressing this

If you're enjoying Bluesky and you don't want it to turn into the cesspool of hate that Twitter did, you best speak up now. Cut that 'I don't know what to say' shit out and amplify Black and queer voices, because the BS team ain't listening to us.

I hope folks angry and annoyed at everyone speaking up about what’s happening here understand it’s actually about saving the platform. If this was about killing the platform or giving up on it we’d all just leave. Like we did with Twitter.

Keep going until this is seen by everyone on this platform:

TechCrunch even called BlueSky out on antiblackness yall.

https://techcrunch.com/2023/06/08/blueskys-growing-pains-strain-relationship-with-its-black-community-moderation/?guccounter=1

I have really loved Bluesky, it has been incredibly pleasant and fun to use and be a part so far.

But even with Twitter on fire and Threadsa nightmare, this place isn't worth putting time, effort and investment into if it won't have basic protections for vulnerable groups, especially black users.
